# ENTITY

## BlogPost

### FEATURES

extends = ["SimpleEntity"]

### DESCRIPTION

Blog article entity. `authorAccountId` references the user account that owns
the draft. `content` stores the canonical HTML article fragment extracted from
full HTML input or accepted directly by `registerPost`. `primaryImageId`
references the image used as the main visual. Additional images are represented
by `EntityImageBinding`, and inline `img` tag occurrences are tracked by
`BlogInlineImage`.

Public read/search should expose only posts whose draft status is published and
whose active status is active. Draft and inactive posts remain author/admin
surfaces.

### ATTRIBUTE

| name            | type     | multiplicity | web-label      | web-placeholder |
|-----------------+----------+--------------+----------------+-----------------|
| id              | entityid | 1            | ID             |                 |
| slug            | string   | 1            | Slug           | release-note    |
| title           | string   | 1            | Title          | Release note    |
| content         | string   | 1            | Content        | HTML fragment   |
| authorAccountId | entityid | 1            | Author account |                 |
| primaryImageId  | entityid | ?            | Primary image  |                 |
| draftStatus     | string   | 1            | Draft status   | Draft           |
| activeStatus    | string   | 1            | Active status  | Active          |

## ImageAsset

### FEATURES

extends = ["SimpleEntity"]

### DESCRIPTION

Image metadata entity. Binary storage is intentionally outside this component;
`objectKey` can point to a BlobStore/S3 object or another repository.

### ATTRIBUTE

| name        | type     | multiplicity | web-label    | web-placeholder          |
|-------------+----------+--------------+--------------+--------------------------|
| id          | entityid | 1            | ID           |                          |
| objectKey   | string   | 1            | Object key   | images/hero.jpg          |
| contentType | string   | 1            | Content type | image/jpeg               |
| altText     | string   | ?            | Alt text     | Product screenshot       |
| width       | int      | ?            | Width        | 1200                     |
| height      | int      | ?            | Height       | 630                      |
| checksum    | string   | ?            | Checksum     | sha256:...               |

## EntityImageBinding

### FEATURES

extends = ["SimpleEntity"]

### DESCRIPTION

Generic link from an Entity instance to an image.

`entityName` plus `entityId` identifies the owner Entity. `role` distinguishes
cover, inline, thumbnail, and other use cases.

### ATTRIBUTE

| name       | type     | multiplicity | web-label   | web-placeholder |
|------------+----------+--------------+-------------+-----------------|
| id         | entityid | 1            | ID          |                 |
| entityName | string   | 1            | Entity      | BlogPost        |
| entityId   | entityid | 1            | Entity ID   |                 |
| imageId    | entityid | 1            | Image ID    |                 |
| role       | string   | 1            | Role        | cover           |
| sortOrder  | int      | ?            | Sort order  | 10              |
| caption    | string   | ?            | Caption     | Figure caption  |

## BlogInlineImage

### FEATURES

extends = ["SimpleEntity"]

### DESCRIPTION

Image occurrence extracted from an `img` tag in a blog article content
fragment.

This entity records source markup details separately from the generic
`EntityImageBinding` link. A synchronized inline image should have a
corresponding `EntityImageBinding` row with `role = inline`.

### ATTRIBUTE

| name         | type     | multiplicity | web-label     | web-placeholder |
|--------------+----------+--------------+---------------+-----------------|
| id           | entityid | 1            | ID            |                 |
| blogPostId   | entityid | 1            | Blog post     |                 |
| imageId      | entityid | ?            | Managed image |                 |
| sourceUrl    | string   | 1            | Source URL    | /blob/content/1 |
| altText      | string   | ?            | Alt text      | Screenshot      |
| titleText    | string   | ?            | Title text    |                 |
| sortOrder    | int      | 1            | Sort order    | 10              |
| synchronized | boolean  | 1            | Synchronized  | true            |

# COMMAND

## ImportPostTree

### DESCRIPTION

User-facing bulk import command. `archiveBlobId` points to a Blob containing a
Blog article file tree. The tree must contain `META-INF/blog.yaml`; metadata in
that file is authoritative, and missing values may fall back to the HTML head.
`treeRootPath` is the local development-driver input for an already expanded
tree.

The entry HTML may be a full HTML document. BlogComponent parses it through CNCF
standard HTML tree values, extracts the article fragment, resolves relative
image paths, and calls `RegisterBlogPost`.

### ATTRIBUTE

| name            | type     | multiplicity |
|-----------------+----------+--------------|
| archiveBlobId   | entityid | ?            |
| treeRootPath    | string   | ?            |
| entryHtmlPath   | string   | ?            |
| authorAccountId | entityid | 1            |
| publish         | boolean  | ?            |

## RegisterBlogPost

### DESCRIPTION

Lower-level bulk registration command. `content` is a normalized HTML fragment.
`entityImages` represents thumbnail/cover/gallery style Entity images.
`inlineImages` represents images embedded in the HTML content.

### ATTRIBUTE

| name            | type                | multiplicity |
|-----------------+---------------------+--------------|
| slug            | string              | 1            |
| title           | string              | ?            |
| content         | string              | 1            |
| authorAccountId | entityid            | 1            |
| publish         | boolean             | ?            |
| description     | string              | ?            |
| canonicalPath   | string              | ?            |
| entityImages    | BlogEntityImageSpec | *            |
| inlineImages    | BlogInlineImageSpec | *            |

